name: Fig. 2 Electron density evidence for four residues adopting conformations in the −35° < ϕ < +35° range.
description: Thesis Series Part 1/3 - This is Figure 2 from my first published paper. I spent MANY MANY hours producing this figure. Possibly more time than I've ever spent on any other visual artifact. This was when I first fell in love with the visual display of information. This figure (and the scientific meaning behind it) can be found in the paper "Native proteins trap high-energy transit conformations" (aka the Mountain Pass paper), doi: 10.1126/sciadv.1501188
